  "issue_number": 3597,
  "issue_title": "AI: add an Equipment / Voltron deck-feature axis + policy",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n`phase-ai` cannot recognize an **equipment-matters / voltron** deck: a dense Equipment package, equip payoffs (equipped-creature buffs, equipment-cast / ETB triggers, equip-cost grants/reducers), and creatures that fetch or auto-attach Equipment (Stoneforge Mystic, Kor Outfitter, Sram, Puresteel Paladin). The AI today values equipment only as generic artifacts and has no plan-level recognition of equipping toward a single threat (voltron) or of equip payoffs. This adds the missing `EquipmentFeature` + payoff-gated policy via the `add-ai-feature-policy` pattern.\n\n## Why it's valuable / necessary\nEquipment decks are a real, recurring archetype: Modern Hammer Time (Colossus Hammer + Sigarda's Aid / Puresteel Paladin), Stoneblade, and Commander voltron. The engine already resolves Equip, equipped-creature statics, and Equipment tutors (verified: Bonesplitter, Puresteel Paladin, Sram, Stoneforge Mystic, Kor Outfitter all parse to the expected typed AST), but the AI has no plan-level recognition.\n\n**Support, measured directly in `card-data.json` (34,771 cards):**\n- **632 cards** carry the `Equipment` subtype (all `Artifact`) \u2014 the fuel.\n- **672 cards** have \"equipped creature\" oracle text \u2014 the equipped-creature-payoff signature.\n\n> An earlier draft cited \"828 cards \u2026 equipment signature.\" That figure is corrected above: the Equipment-subtype class is ~632 and the equipped-creature-payoff-text class is ~672. Still comfortably axis-worthy \u2014 comparable to the merged reanimator axis (~683) \u2014 but the support claim is now honest.\n\n## Current behavior\n`DeckFeatures::analyze` (`features/mod.rs`) has no equipment axis \u2014 Equipment falls under generic artifact valuation (`features/artifacts.rs` values artifact *count* / affinity-improvise payoffs, with zero equip-payoff or voltron awareness). On the policy side, equipment is **not** entirely unhandled:\n- `policies/equipment_priority.rs` (`PolicyId::EquipmentPriority`, registered) already exists \u2014 but it is an **anti-over-equipping guard**: it *rejects* wasteful same-host re-equips and strict downgrades (the Skullclamp #1986 bug) and, by design, \"never *rewards* equipping.\"\n\nSo nothing values the voltron plan, equip payoffs, or equipment density \u2014 but the equip decision is already partly governed. **Integration note:** the proposed policy *rewards* equipping, which fires on the same `DecisionKind::ActivateAbility` / `WaitingFor::EquipTarget` decisions that `EquipmentPriorityPolicy` penalizes. The two sum in the registry, so the new policy must be calibrated to encourage *fresh* equips / voltron concentration **without** overriding the over-equip guard's rejection of pointless re-equips (analogous to the reanimator \u2194 `mill_targeting` self-mill interaction).\n\n## Correct behavior\nAn `EquipmentFeature` detects (parts-based, no card-name matching):\n- **Equipment density** \u2014 a face whose `card_type.subtypes` contains `\"Equipment\"` (`TypeFilter::Subtype(\"Equipment\")`; there is no `TypeFilter::Equipment` variant). The fuel.\n- **Equip payoffs:**\n  - equipped-creature buff statics \u2014 a `StaticDefinition` whose `affected` `TypedFilter` carries `FilterProp::EquippedBy` (`crates/engine/src/types/ability.rs:2331`), e.g. Bonesplitter's \"Equipped creature gets +2/+0\";\n  - equip-cost grants / reducers \u2014 a static whose `modifications` add/cheapen the `Equip` keyword on your Equipment (e.g. Puresteel Paladin's `AddKeyword { Equip { generic: 0 } }`);\n  - equipment-cast / ETB payoffs \u2014 a `SpellCast` or `ChangesZone` trigger whose `valid_card` filter is the Equipment subtype (e.g. Sram, Puresteel's draw);\n  - equipment enablers \u2014 `Effect::Attach` (auto-equip, Kor Outfitter) and `Effect::SearchLibrary` for Equipment (tutors, Stoneforge Mystic).\n\nA companion **payoff-gated** `TacticalPolicy` raises the value of deploying Equipment, equipping a creature (concentrating buffs = voltron), and casting equipment payoffs when the deck is equipment-committed; inert otherwise.\n\n## Design \u2014 follow the thin payoff precedent (lifegain / enchantments / reanimator)\nBuild at the scale the logic genuinely needs, matching the freshly-blessed thin feature-+-payoff pattern (the reanimator axis merged this way in #3595):\n- `features/reanimator.rs` + `policies/reanimator_payoff.rs` + `PolicyId::ReanimatorPayoff` (the most recent reference)\n- `features/lifegain.rs` (183 ln) + `policies/lifegain_payoff.rs`; `features/enchantments.rs` (199 ln) + `policies/enchantments_payoff.rs`\n\n1. **New `crates/phase-ai/src/features/equipment.rs`** \u2014 `pub struct EquipmentFeature { equipment_count, payoff_count, commitment }` + structural `detect()` over `CardFace.card_type.subtypes` (Equipment), `static_abilities` (`FilterProp::EquippedBy` buffs / Equip-keyword grants), and `triggers` (Equipment-cast / ETB). Payoff-weighted commitment, requiring both equipment density AND a payoff so a single incidental Equipment stays inert (mirror the reanimator two-pillar geometric-mean shape).\n2. **`features/mod.rs`** \u2014 `pub mod equipment;`, re-export, `DeckFeatures` field, `analyze()` wiring.\n3. **New `crates/phase-ai/src/policies/equipment_payoff.rs`** \u2014 payoff-gated `TacticalPolicy`, new UNTUNED `PolicyPenalties` knob, calibrated to coexist with `EquipmentPriorityPolicy` (reward fresh equips/voltron, not pointless re-equips).\n4. **`policies/registry.rs`** \u2014 `PolicyId::EquipmentPayoff` + registration.\n5. **Single authority** \u2014 `pub(crate) fn is_equip_payoff(...)` / `is_equipment(...)` shared by detector and policy via parts predicates over `GameObject` fields.\n6. **Duel suite / gate coverage** \u2014 add `FeatureKind::Equipment` (and to `FeatureKind::ALL`); bump `feature_kind_matches_deck_features_field_count`; add the new feature to a matchup's `exercises` + an `#[ignore]` floor-crossing test. **Unlike reanimator (which reused the existing `greasefang-mirror`), there is no existing equipment duel deck** \u2014 this requires **building a new Hammer-Time / Stoneblade `duel_decks/modern/*.json` snapshot** from engine-supported card names, verified to (a) load (`every_snapshot_loads` needs \u226540 resolvable cards) and (b) clear `COMMITMENT_FLOOR` *before* committing. This is the main effort sink; scope for it.\n7. **Tests in SEPARATE files** \u2014 impl files contain **no** `#[cfg(test)]`; declare the test submodule from the parent `mod.rs`, never from the impl file.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `EquipmentFeature` detects equipment density + equip payoffs (parts-based, not name-matching), wired into `DeckFeatures::analyze`.\n- [ ] A payoff-gated `equipment_payoff` `TacticalPolicy` registered in `PolicyRegistry::default`, calibrated to coexist with `EquipmentPriorityPolicy` (no override of the over-equip rejection).\n- [ ] `FeatureKind::Equipment` added; an equipment matchup is in the **required** gate, with an `#[ignore]` test asserting the deck clears `COMMITMENT_FLOOR`, and the regenerated baseline shows it as a real PASS row (policy active).\n- [ ] Detector + policy tests in separate files (impl files inline-test-free); calibration anchors included.\n- [ ] No `no_name_matching` / `score_contract` lint violation; `PolicyPenalties` field-coverage passes (UNTUNED knob).\n\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-17T15:34:32.000Z",
